        "amlCft": [
          "Yes",
          "<p>The Money Laundering, Terrorist Financing, and Transfer of Funds Regulations 2017 are applicable to digital asset service providers.<p>The activities that come under the regulatory perimeter are digital asset exchange providers, digital assets ATMs, digital asset issuers and custodian wallet providers.<p>The entities must undertake KYC requirements and monitor and report suspicious transactions through Suspicious Activity Reports.<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) has also issued guidance on how digital asset exchange and custodian wallet providers can comply with AML/CFT requirements. The guidance specifically lists factors that digital asset service providers should consider as high-risk when from an AML/CFT perspective. It specifies that digital assets that provide privacy-enhancing features or products and services that obfuscate transactions should be considered high risk.<p>While the FCA has not banned any specific digital assets, certain digital asset service providers, such as Kraken have stoped offering privacy coins like Monero.<p>Source(s):<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/economic-crime-and-corporate-transparency-bill-2022-factsheets/fact-sheet-cryptoassets-technical\">GOV.UK Technical Factsheet : Cryptoassets</a><br />2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/cryptoassets-manual/crypto100350\">HMRC Cryptoassets Manual</a><br />3. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.jmlsg.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Consultation-review-version-Part-II-Sector-22_Cryptoasset-exchange-and-custodian-wallet-providers_Board-approved-March-2020.pdf\">Consultation Review - Cryptoasset exchange providers</a><br />4. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/currencies/monero-kraken-crypto-exchange-delist-privacy-coin-uk-fca-regulation-2021-11\">BusinessInsider - Kraken delists Monero</a></p>\n"
        ],
        "grievanceRedressal": [
          "Partial - General Legislation",
          "<p>The Consumer Rights Act 2015 may apply to businesses that provide services and products to consumers, including digital asset service providers.<p>However, there are no specific requirements for consumer protection.<p>His Majesty's Treasury's proposed regulatory framework for digital assets would require digital asset service providers to comply with consumer protection requirements that include creating adequate procedures for handling consumer complaints.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2015/15/section/1/enacted\" target=\"_blank\">Consumer Rights Act, 2015 </a><br />2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-financial-services-regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets\" target=\"_blank\">HMT Consultation and call for evidence: Future financial services regulatory regime for cryptoassets</a><br /></p>\n"
        ],
        "dataProtection": [
          "Partial - General Legislation",
          "<p>Currently, digital asset service providers may qualify as data controllers or processors under the Data Protection Act, 2018.<p>There are no other information security or data protection requirements specifically for digital asset service providers.<p>However, His Majesty's Treasury's proposed framework would require digital asset service providers to ensure they have the relevant resources and personnel to ensure operational resilience. It also prescribes the adoption of effective &quot;cyber security protections&quot;.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2018/12/contents/enacted\" target=\"_blank\">Data Protection Act, 2018 </a><br />2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-financial-services-regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets\" target=\"_blank\">HMT Consultation and call for evidence: Future financial services regulatory regime for cryptoassets </a></p>\n"
        ],
        "advertisingRegulations": [
          "Yes",
          "<p>Ads for digital assets are a &ldquo;red alert&rdquo; priority issue for The Advertising Standards Authority (ASA).<p>Entities promoting digital assets must make it expressly clear in the ad that:<br />\n1. Digital assets are unregulated in the UK.<br />\n2. Digital asset profits may be subject to Capital Gains Tax.<br />\n3. The value of investments is variable and can go down as well as up.<p>His Majesty's Treasury's proposed framework would create a detailed framework governing the promotion and offering of digital assets to citizens. This would include informing users of:<p>1. the features of the digital asset<br />\n2. rights and obligations attached to the asset<br />\n3. outline of the underlying technology<br />\n4. details of the person issuing the token or seeking admission on the trading venue.<p>Source(s):<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.asa.org.uk/news/enforcement-notice-advertising-of-cryptocurrencies.html\" target=\"_blank\">Enforcement Notice: advertising of cryptocurrencies</a><br />2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-financial-services-regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets\" target=\"_blank\">HMT Consultation and call for evidence: Future financial services regulatory regime for cryptoassets </a></p>\n"
        ],
        "consumerAwareness": [
          "Proposed",
          "<p>Increasing consumer awareness was cited as a key area for increased policy action in the Crytpoasset Taskforce Report.<p>The financial regulators have issued several warnings, advisories and guidances to improve consumer awareness of the risks associated with digital assets.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cryptoassets-taskforce\">Cryptoassets Taskforce: final report </a><br />2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.fca.org.uk/news/statements/initial-coin-offerings\">Initial Coin Offerings - Financial Conduct Authority </a></p>\n"
        ],
        "investorProtection": [
          "No",
          "<p>Digital assets are generally not covered by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme - which provides insurance against the loss of financial holdings.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.fscs.org.uk/news/protection/cryptocurrencies-risk-cover/\">FCFS</a></p>\n"
        ],
        "restrictions": [
          "Yes",
          "<p>The FCA has banned the offering of digital asset derivates to retail users due to their high volatility.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.fca.org.uk/news/press-releases/fca-bans-sale-crypto-derivatives-retail-consumers\">FCA ban on sale of crypto-derivatives to retail consumers</a></p>\n"
        ],
