          "<p>The Securities and Exchanges Commission, Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, and Federal Trade Commission have received and acted on consumer complaints related to digital assets. Complaints filed by consumers relate to fraud, transaction issues, customer service issues, frozen accounts and bankruptcies, and advertising.<p>Source:<br />\n1. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.sec.gov/spotlight/cybersecurity-enforcement-actions\">SEC Enforcement Actions</a><br/>\n2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/documents/cfpb_complaint-bulletin_crypto-assets_2022-11.pdf\">CFPB Complaints Bulletin </a><br/>\n\n2. <a target=\"_blank\"  href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-12-05/ftc-investigates-crypto-firms-over-misleading-advertising?sref=323RPL5z&leadSource=uverify%20wall\">Bloomberg</a></p>\n"
